&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;We are a team of highly-driven individuals who are passionate about technology, algorithmic trading, and solving intellectually challenging problems. Being a part of Sparkland means you get to work with some of the brightest people in one of the world’s fastest-growing and most exciting industries. We are fully remote and have a flat corporate structure that values open-mindedness, entrepreneurial spirit, commitment to excellence, and continuous learning.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3&gt;The role&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;page&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;section&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;layoutArea&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;column&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for entrepreneurial, competitive, and analytical talent to join our Trading department. You do not need to have a financial background; we will teach you all you need to know. You will solve problems, create new tools, and/or design new strategies. If you have 1-3 years of experience coding, excellent mental arithmetic and analytical skills, and a genuine interest in learning algorithmic and quantitative trading you might be a good candidate for this role. Having trading knowledge or experience isn’t required for the role, but a genuine interest in learning algorithmic, high-frequency, and quantitative trading is helpful.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Trade a wide range of financial instruments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop, maintain and improve trading strategies and algorithms. Run trading desks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage the execution and risk of complex trading portfolios.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run projects with developers from the IT department.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Education&lt;/strong&gt;: Graduated in 2023–2025, preferably in a STEM field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills&lt;/strong&gt;: Strong mental arithmetic and analytical abilities (tested).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Coding&lt;/strong&gt;: 1–3 years of experience in any programming language, including at least 1 year of professional/commercial work (tested).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Knowledge&lt;/strong&gt;: Solid understanding of data structures, algorithms, and design patterns.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Language&lt;/strong&gt;: Fluent in English.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Flexibility&lt;/strong&gt;: Open to relocation to Dubai.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bonus Points&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participation in national competitions is desirable.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High grades are a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Trading knowledge or experience isn’t required, but a genuine interest in learning algorithmic, high-frequency, and quantitative trading is helpful.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
